caption: (Translated by Google) Excellent place to eat as a family.  (Original) Excelente lugar para comer en familia.

Very neat and accessible restaurant. They provide large meals and for economical rates. I enjoyed the food a lot and the staff members were very amiable and explanatory. Recommended.
Excellent. The people that worked there were great.

Great service and good food! Staff and manager were so friendly and accommodating. Set up the outdoor heaters to accommodate our party. At the end, the manager gave all the kids a whole box of candy canes!
The chef and host there were great. I'll most certainly be back for more.

Regarding the KBBQ Experience:  Coming in, I expected the standard KBBQ set up. For the all you can eat price, you can only get one type of meat, beef brisket, which was served frozen on the table. The side dishes were bland and although look good, essentially non-edible. We were also served rice which was cold and clearly not fresh. If you want an authentic KBBQ experience, please avoid this place, especially if you have experience with this sort of food.  I can’t speak for the other food they offer since all I had was the KBBQ. The staff were friendly and courteous.

I love the food but the customer service is below par. Purple rice bowl with a protein. Add the carrots, kale and etc, and it's so bomb. Top it off with some ginger carrot sauce, sooo good.  There is a manager who is too busy being in everyone else's conversations and being rude, then actually helping. This manager does make you test your faith. Sometimes its not worth the headache. The food is starting to fall off in the freshness department.  So glad she's not my boss. I feel sorry for the ppl who have to work with her.
Great gluten free options

I ordered from DoorDash tonight and it was horrible! Food was cold, the chicken was bland, and it came with more noodles than anything else. Horrible experience! I’m only giving it two stars because I know they’re better than this, cause I’ve ordered from them in the past, or else they would’ve gotten one star.

It was laid back, filling and delicious.  You get unlimited beef and banchan, but have the options for other items if you want that instead.  The staff was friendly, and helpful.  If you're in the mood for a different kind of dinner, with great korean flavor this is worth your time.

Delicious Korean food bursting with flavor! Truly a vegetarian's delight, the Herbivore is loaded up with veggies - Kalbi-tofu, bean sprouts, corn, carrots, cucumbers, pickled radish, kale slaw, kimichi, crispy garlic, scallions, roasted sesame seeds, and swapped out the ginger carrot sauce for the cilantro lime ranch and added the avocado. The salad was filled to the brim and threw in the towel before I could make it to the end! The Kale Apple juice is sweet and refreshing with no added sugar. The service was warm and welcoming. Highly recommend!

would LOVE the chance to take a moment and RAVE about SouelSpice!! I just arrived in DC at my hotel and was hungry. My friend looked up a few resturants in the area and he found SeoulSpice. After reviewing the menu, we decided to go and check this place out. NOW The location is AMAZING, CLEANLINESS is INSANE, STAFF OUT of this WORLD and Most Important FOOD IS JAW DROPPINGLY GOOD!!. I wanted to eat my bowl and not the food that was in it, but the bowl when I was done and my friend wanted to devour his box also. I went in around 6:00 PM and was helped by Francis who I must say is one of the kindest people you can meet. Even when he was not helping someone he was Smiling along with the other staff. He helped my friend and I understand the menu so we could better get an idea of what we wanted to order and allowed us to try the different meat. We decided on the Seoul Train Bowl and my friend got a Kimchi Kruch Korrito!! Now let me say, right beside this Hidden Jewel is another guy who offers a mexican type of bowl that doesn't compeate. SeoulSpice moved my soul and actually going to Busan and Souel Korea, it reminded me of a memory and also made a lasting one! I will be there today to get some food to take back home to Hampton, Virginia!!! I wish you was everywhere and I truly wish this company the best success. If the culture here is anything like the other locations, this resturant will be sure to success. TRULY and proud to say my entire government REGINALD JAMES NEELY II

I've tried this place a few times in the past 3 years.  On my first few visits this place would have gotten a 2 star rating.  The food was just okay and the interaction with the staff was subpar (I felt like I was an irritation they had to deal with).  I kept wanting to like this place (and have something different) so I would check back every so often.  Lately it seems like the staff (new people) has been more consistent (and nicer) and developed a certain rhythm that has made the experience more enjoyable and the food seems to taste better.  Hands down though, if I have to choose between this and bibibop, I'm going to bibibop.... but once in a while I'll keep giving seoul spice the opportunity to impress more.

I'm a regular customer at this location. I always come in here and get a bowl and a drink. I've never had any complaints about the food. I love the people that work there they are very friendly and we always have a great time when I come to Seoul spice. But tonight when I went in there. a new lady there  immediately gave me bad vibes. As soon as I walk through the door she looked at me like I had five heads. Everyone else in the store spoke to me like they normally would and when I look at her she rolled her eyes. I had mentioned to one of the employees that if someone was to stare you in your face they should at least speak. The girls then proceeded to yell and scream profanities across the restaurant at me saying that I can get the hell out of her store. I then told her I am a paying customer. She then told me to get my s*** and get out. How rude is that. I spend my hard-earned money in this restaurant more than five nights a week because it is so close to my residence. I love the food and atmosphere the scenery the people in this restaurant. Why is it all of a sudden I'm being cursed and yelled at in front of a restaurant full of people. I then went to the bathroom use the bathroom came back out to the restaurant and sat at a table. the manager then proceeded to walk out to me and tell me to get out of her store again. she had already called the police on me and said that they were on the way.I asked her if all of this is necessary. She told me I was disrupting her store yelling and acting crazy. I then looked around and asked who is being crazy everyone in the store looked at the store manager. I'm not really understanding what I did so wrong to have the police called on me to be yelled and cursed at somewhere where I'm coming to spend my money. The police then arrived to Seoul spice to remove me from the store. She then rolled her neck head and eyes like she had done something spectacular...lol It was such an embarrassing experience. I wouldn't wish this on my worst enemy. I just don't get why the police were involved number one number two the store manager was so rude and number three I didn't even get to take my food outside. I then left the store and was outside when one of the customers from the store told me that the store manager threatened me and said that if I ever came back in the store she would kick my ass. She also said.she would fight me when she gets off. This is just ridiculous. And im very shocked Seoul spice has people who act like this in their store....im very offended...im a mother of 2 and pregnant.  What do i look like fighting someone who cant even speak when you walk into their store to spend your money....im baffled....oh and how am i supposed to bring my kids there to eat if im going to get my ass kicked...smh its a shame i know this cant be legal....👀

In general I'm not a fan of Korean food, but I thought I'd give the place a try, and I'm glad I did. I got one of their suggested bowls (you have a Subway-like option of building whatever you want) and found it to be quite good. There was a good balance between rice, meat, and vegetables and probably the most important piece to me, sauce. I hate it when my food ends up being dry because a restaurant is stingy with its sauce, but I also dislike it when my food is bathing in sauce and it becomes the only thing I can taste. Maybe I got lucky this time, but they nailed the balance for me. Hopefully you have the same experience.

(Translated by Google) Very good "Korean fusion" restaurant. It is a fast food restaurant with 4 dishes to choose from: bibimpap (bowl of rice), kimbap (seaweed leaf with rice inside and others), tacos or salad. You then choose between beef, chicken, pork or tofu. And finally, your vegetables, sauces etc. For me who lived in Korea, and for my Korean wife, we were pleasantly surprised. The quality is good, the staff helpful and the place pleasant. If you are looking for traditional Korean cuisine, it is best to go elsewhere. If you're ready to try a mix, come on!  (Original) Très bon restaurant de "fusion korean". Il s'agit de restauration rapide avec 4 plats au choix : bibimpap  (bol de riz), kimbap  (feuille d'algue avec du riz dedans et autres), tacos ou salade. Vous choisissez ensuite entre le boeuf,  le poulet, le porc ou le tofu. Et enfin, vos légumes,  sauces etc. Pour moi qui ait vécu en Corée, et pour mon épouse coréenne, nous avons été agréablement surpris. La qualité est bonne, le personnel serviable et l'endroit agréable. Si vous cherchez de la cuisine traditionnelle coréenne,  il vaut mieux aller ailleurs. Si vous êtes prêts à essayer un mix, venez-y !
